text:
getInitParameter() of ServletConfig always returns null.  Web.xml is as follows:
<web-app>
<servlet>
  <servlet-name>NSREntryServlet</servlet-name>
  <servlet-class>com.harris.nsr.NSREntryServlet</servlet-class>
    <init-param>
      <param-name>DB_URI_KEY</param-name>
      <param-value>jdbc:odbc:nsr</param-value>
    </init-param>
  <load-on-startup>1</load-on-startup>
</servlet>
</web-app>

Code snippet of action servlet is as follows:
ServletConfig conf = getServletConfig();//get the servlet config obj
		try
		{
		  outputStream = new PrintWriter(new FileOutputStream
("c:\\temp\\Initialized.log"));

			outputStream.println("NSREntryServlet initialized.");
			outputStream.println(" ");
			outputStream.print("DB_URI_KEY value = ");
			outputStream.println(conf.getInitParameter
("DB_URI_KEY"));
		}
		catch(FileNotFoundException e)
		{
			System.out.println("Error opening the file");
			System.exit(0);
		}

		outputStream.close();
